-- Aramex Plans 4-5 Acquisitions by First Quarter in Asia, Africa, CEO Says
-- B y   S t e f a n i a   B i a n c h i
-- 2010-11-08T06:02:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/aramex-plans-4-5-acquisitions-by-first-quarter-in-asia-africa-ceo-says.html
Aramex PJSC, the United Arab
Emirates-based courier company, will make four to five
acquisitions by the first quarter of 2011 in Asia and Africa,
Chief Executive Officer Fadi Ghandour said in Dubai today.  The company has about $100 million to spend over the next
two to three years, Ghandour said. Aramex expects at least three
acquisitions by the year end, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefania Bianchi in Dubai at 
 sbianchi10@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
